14/08/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- Police said in a report published Thursday (August 13th) that crime is up sharply this year, compared to 2008. Burglaries have increased by 41% this year, and bank robberies are up by 43.2% from last year. According to the report, about 80% of all crimes occur in Athens and Thessaloniki. The main reason appears to be the economic crisis. (Vima, BTA, MRT - 13/08/09)
